{{Infobox university |name= Irell & Manella Graduate School of Biological Sciences |image= Emblem of City of Hope's Irell & Manella Graduate School of Biological Sciences.png |image_size= 125px |motto= |endowment= |dean= John J. Rossi, Ph.D. |chancellor= |provost= |former_names = |established= 1994 |type= [[Graduate school]] |faculty= 59 |staff= |students= 80 |undergrad= |postgrad= |nickname= |mascot= |colors= |city= [[Duarte, California|Duarte]] |state= [[California]] |country= [[United States]] |campus= [[Medical school]] |free_label= |free= |website= http://cityofhope.org/education/grad-school/ |logo= }}
The '''Irell & Manella Graduate School of Biological Sciences''' (formerly the '''City of Hope Graduate School of Biological Sciences''') is a graduate school for biology in the [[City of Hope National Medical Center]] in [[Duarte, California|Duarte]], [[California]].
==Program== The [[Irell & Manella]] Graduate School of Biological Sciences is a doctoral-only program that trains students to become research scientists with expertise in [[chemical biology|chemical]], [[molecular biology|molecular]], and [[cellular biology]]. Graduates of this program are awarded the degree of [[Doctor of Philosophy]] ([[Ph.D.]]) in Biological Sciences, and as such are equipped to address fundamental questions in the [[life science]]s and [[biomedicine]]. Most graduates pursue careers in [[academia]], [[industry]], or [[government]].<ref>[http://www.cityofhope.org/education/grad-school/Pages/home.aspx City of Hope Irell & Manella Graduate School of Biological Sciences - Biology Graduate School, Cancer Biology Graduate School] "Our students have gone on to illustrious careers at major universities, research institutions, pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies."</ref>
The school is housed at the [[Beckman Research Institute]] of the City of Hope National Medical Center. It is accredited by the Accrediting Commission for Senior Colleges and Universities of the [[Western Association of Schools and Colleges]].<ref>[http://www.cityofhope.org/education/grad-school/Pages/home.aspx City of Hope Irell & Manella Graduate School of Biological Sciences - Biology Graduate School, Cancer Biology Graduate School] "In 2001, the school was accredited by national and regional accrediting bodies recognized by the U.S. Department of Education."</ref>
